ruin","hidden-gem"]},{"name":"Carnasserie Castle","county":"Argyll and Bute","type":"tower house","condition":"ruin","era":"16th century","rating":3.9,"reviewCount":670,"access":"free","description":"A fine Renaissance tower house built by John Carswell, who published the first book printed in Gaelic. Its carved details and fireplaces show French architectural influence.","image":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/74/Carnasserie_Castle_-_geograph.org.uk_-_7881916.jpg/500px-Carnasserie_Castle_-_geograph.org.uk_-_7881916.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/carnasserie-castle-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/carnasserie-castle-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/carnasserie-castle-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/carnasserie-castle-5.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/carnasserie-castle-main-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/carnasserie-castle-main-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/carnasserie-castle-main-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/carnasserie-castle-main-5.jpg"],"tags":["romantic-ruin","hidden-gem","free"]},{"name":"Skipness Castle","county":"Argyll and Bute","type":"castle","condition":"ruin","era":"13th century","rating":3.9,"reviewCount":560,"access":"free","description":"A 13th-century castle on the east shore of Kintyre with views across the Kilbrannan Sound to Arran. The adjacent chapel contains fine medieval carved grave slabs.","image":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/74/Skipness_Castle_%28September_2023%29.jpg/500px-Skipness_Castle_%28September_2023%29.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/skipness-castle-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/skipness-castle-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/skipness-castle-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/skipness-castle-5.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/skipness-castle-main-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/skipness-castle-main-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/skipness-castle-main-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/skipness-castle-main-5.jpg"],"tags":["romantic-ruin",