anded three seas — and one of Scotland's bloodiest massacres unfolded.","image":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/26/Dunaverty_-_geograph.org.uk_-_735878.jpg/500px-Dunaverty_-_geograph.org.uk_-_735878.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/dunaverty-castle-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/dunaverty-castle-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/dunaverty-castle-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/dunaverty-castle-5.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/dunaverty-castle-main-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/dunaverty-castle-main-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/dunaverty-castle-main-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/dunaverty-castle-main-5.jpg"],"tags":["cliffside","coastal","remote","dark-brooding","atmospheric","medieval"]},{"name":"Fraoch Eilean Castle","county":"Argyll and Bute","type":"castle","condition":"ruin","era":"13th century","rating":3.3,"reviewCount":35,"access":"free","description":"A ruined island castle in Loch Awe, surrounded by ancient legend and accessible only by boat. One of several atmospheric strongholds dotting this vast Highland loch.","image":"https://img.castlecore.uk/fraoch-eilean-castle.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/fraoch-eilean-castle-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/fraoch-eilean-castle-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/fraoch-eilean-castle-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/fraoch-eilean-castle-5.jpg"],"tags":["ruins-romantic","island","remote","atmospheric","free-entry"]},{"name":"Dun Carloway Broch","county":"Western Isles","type":"broch","condition":"ruin","era":"Iron Age (c. 100 BC)","rating":4.1,"reviewCount":155,"access":"free","description":"A dramatically situated Iron Age broch on the west coast of Lewis, one of the best-preserved in Scotland. Ancient stonework against a backdrop of Atlantic sky and moorland.","image":"https://img.castlecore.uk/dun-carloway-broch.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/dun-carloway-broch-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/dun-carloway-broch-3.jpg","https://img.c